  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Real-Time Architecture**\n\nI\'m now contemplating the server-side architecture. The key decision is how to handle real-time state. Should I lean towards WebSockets, or would Server-Sent Events be a more suitable option? I need to analyze the pros and cons of each in this specific use case.\n\n\n**Evaluating WebSocket Implementation**\n\nI\'ve decided to move forward with WebSockets, and my focus is now on implementation. Since `ws` isn\'t currently a dependency, I\'m going to install it and its types, with the help of the `install_applet_package` tool. The app will be running in an Express server inside a container on port 3000, so `ws` should work perfectly.\n\n\n**Prioritizing SSE Simplicity**\n\nI\'m now re-evaluating the architecture, and Server-Sent Events (SSE) has emerged as the leading contender. The focus shifts to its inherent simplicity and compatibility, especially considering Cloud Run\'s environment. The use of standard HTTP and its lightweight nature makes it very appealing. This approach reduces dependency conflicts, especially on React 19. It simplifies the design, especially given that Cloud Run is the deployment platform.\n\n\n**Designing the Application**\n\nI\'m now diving into the application design, starting with the naming. I\'ve decided on \"Kripto Sohbet\" (Encrypted Chat) for a clean, literal name reflecting its purpose, which I\'ll implement by modifying `metadata.json`. Next, I\'m focusing on the visual design, aiming for a sleek, dark, high-contrast UI that conveys a sense of security and privacy. I\'m also planning smooth transitions with `motion` for the messages, and clear typography throughout.\n\n\n**Refining UI Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the UI\'s font selections and responsiveness, using Inter and JetBrains Mono for a clean visual hierarchy, especially for displaying encrypted information. I\'m also planning a responsive layout with a side panel for room configuration to transition gracefully to the chat screen. I also plan to add an end-to-end encryption interface. I\'ll implement a React interface to handle the username, room name, and shared key.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 8
      nanos: 791507242
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
