  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Server**\n\nOkay, I\'m now focusing on the architecture of `/server.ts`. I\'m targeting an Express backend to handle real-time room communication via Server-Sent Events, plus serving the React client. I need to figure out the right way to design that architecture.\n\n\n**Implementing Persistence**\n\nI\'ve made progress on data persistence. I\'m now structuring a local JSON file, `./kripto_sohbet_db.json`, to store room data. It\'ll allow for the dev server to be restarted without losing the current test rooms and messages. I will implement robust read/write. I am also working on SSE and how to send the initial full list of encrypted messages.\n\n\n**Refining Real-Time Updates**\n\nI\'ve been refining the real-time update system. I\'m focusing on SSE implementation; I\'ve got the initial message load wired up, and am now working through handling subscriber lists and managing connections. I\'m thinking I\'ve found a robust way to broadcast new messages and handle client disconnects cleanly. I am also working on adding the POST routes to handle sending and clearing the rooms.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 11
      nanos: 697358992
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
